brainly_data.question: How do capillaries interact with the respiratory system? make sure to mention specific structures of the respiratory system. refer back to your graphic organizer if you need help remembering key anatomy?
brainly_data.subject: Biology

all_answers.question: How do capillaries interact with the respiratory system? make sure to mention specific structures of the respiratory system. refer back to your graphic organizer if you need help remembering key anatomy?
all_answers.subject: Biology
all_answers.text:
Capillary interact with the respiratory system by allowing gas exchange to the alveolus. The gas inside the capillary is high in carbon dioxide and low in oxygen, but gas in alveolus is high in oxygen and low in carbon dioxide. 
The capillary will release CO2 and takes O2 as the result.
